content:
Organize Reports

Keep your reports at your fingertips by sorting them into folders and deleting unused reports. You can use the search field to find the one you need.

You can customize report lists in Lightning Experience, and resize, hide, reorder, and sort columns on the Reports tab in Salesforce Classic.

Available in: Essentials, Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

Search for Reports and Dashboards in Lightning Experience by name. To refine your results, sort or search within a selected folder.

When using report and dashboard search in Salesforce Classic, look for a report by name, description, or who created it or modified it last. Filter, sort, or search within a selected folder to refine your results.

You can resize, hide, reorder, and sort columns on the Reports tab list view in Salesforce Classic.

Customize Report and Dashboard Lists in Lightning Experience by customizing the columns in the list on the Reports or Dashboards tab.

Rename a Report from report properties.

Describe a Report with a description to help people distinguish it.

Print a Report from the run page of a report using your browser's print function.

Keep Favorite Report Folders in View by pinning them to the top of the folder list.

Hide Unused Report Types if users only use a subset of available standard report types.

Run Reports in the Background for large reports that might otherwise time out due to large results.

Deliver Your Report by sharing its URL, making it available on Chatter feeds, or exporting data to another tool.

Embedded Report Charts can be embedded in detail pages for objects to give users valuable information directly on the pages they visit often.

Delete a Report from the Reports tab or its run page.
title: Organize and Manage Reports in Salesforce Analytics
